memberdef.argsstring: (const uint8_t i2cSlv4En, const uint8_t i2cSlv4IntEn, const uint8_t i2cSlv4RegDis, const uint8_t i2cSlv4Dly)
memberdef.name: imuJoinI2cSlv4Ctrl

detaileddescription.para:
imuJoinI2cSlv4Ctrl
i2cSlv4En
1 Enable data transfer with this slave at the sample rate. If read command, store data in I2C_SLV4_DI register, if write command, write data stored in I2C_SLV4_DO register. Bit is cleared when a single transfer is complete. Be sure to write I2C_SLV4_DO first. 0 Function is disabled for this slave.
i2cSlv4IntEn
1 Enables the completion of the I2C slave 4 data transfer to cause an interrupt. 0 Completion of the I2C slave 4 data transfer will not cause an interrupt.
i2cSlv4RegDis
When set, the transaction does not write a register value, it will only read data, or write data.
i2cSlv4Dly
When enabled via the I2C_MST_DELAY_CTRL, those slaves will only be enabled every 1/(1+I2C_SLV4_DLY) samples as determined by I2C_MST_ODR_CONFIG

memberdef.argsstring: (const uint8_t int1Actl, const uint8_t int1Open, const uint8_t int1LatchEn, const uint8_t int1Anyrd2Clear, const uint8_t int1FsyncLvl, const uint8_t int1FsyncEn, const uint8_t int1BypassEn)
memberdef.name: imuJoinIntPinCfg

detaileddescription.para:
imuJoinIntPinCfg
int1Actl
1 - The logic level for INT1 pin is active low. 0 - The logic level for INT1 pin is active high.
int1Open
1 - INT1 pin is configured as open drain. 0 - INT1 pin is configured as push-pull.
int1LatchEn
1 - INT1 pin level held until interrupt status is cleared. 0 - INT1 pin indicates interrupt pulse is width 50 s.
int1Anyrd2Clear
1 - Interrupt status in INT_STATUS is cleared (set to 0) if any read operation is performed. 0 - Interrupt status in INT_STATUS is cleared (set to 0) only by reading INT_STATUS register. This bit only affects the interrupt status bits that are contained in the register INT_STATUS, and the corresponding hardware interrupt. This bit does not affect the interrupt status bits that are contained in registers INT_STATUS_1, INT_STATUS_2, INT_STATUS_3, and the corresponding hardware interrupt.
int1FsyncLvl
1 - The logic level for the FSYNC pin as an interrupt to the ICM-20948 is active low. 0 - The logic level for the FSYNC pin as an interrupt to the ICM-20948 is active high.
int1FsyncEn
1 - This enables the FSYNC pin to be used as an interrupt. A transition to the active level described by the ACTL_FSYNC bit will cause an interrupt. The status of the interrupt is read in the I2C Master Status register PASS_THROUGH bit. 0 - This disables the FSYNC pin from causing an interrupt.
int1BypassEn
When asserted, the I2C_MASTER interface pins (ES_CL and ES_DA) will go into bypass mode when the I2C master interface is disabled
